</p>
<figcaption>You can watch the new trailer yourself right here.<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0MxBFXH2a_U" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>


<p>The trailer ends with a look at a bunch of pre-order bonuses you can get by dropping some cash early on Halo: Campaign Evolved. This includes some physical goodies like a statue, five days early access so you can re-experience the 25-year-old story earlier than other Halo fans, and some weapon and armour cosmetics for the single-player only game.</p><p>Snark aside, it's not a huge surprise that this trailer was captured on a PS5 Pro. This year's Summer Game Fest featured <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/playstation-state-of-play-footage-on-ps5-pro-analysis">a substantial number of reveals captured on the system</a>, nearly breaking the record for PS5 Pro representation since the console was revealed.</p>
<p>Halo: Campaign Evolved may be one of the last single-player Microsoft games headed to PlayStation platforms for the foreseeable future, courtesy of new Xbox CEO <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/xbox-console-exclusive-strategy-clockwork-revolution-gears-of-war-e-day">Asha Sharma's push towards more console exclusives</a>. Single player games which haven't already been announced for the PS5 - like <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/xboxs-gears-of-war-e-day-and-clockwork-revolution-are-not-timed-exclusives-as-playstation-5-misses-out-on-upcoming-releases">Gears of War: E-Day and Clockwork Revolution - will be Xbox only from here on out</a>. A bold move, for certain.</p>

